section.section:
The provisions of paragraph (1) of this subsection apply to any violation of any of the following provisions of this subtitle:
§ 21-256(1) of this subtitle, concerning the manufacture or sale of an adulterated or misbranded article;
§ 21-256(2) of this subtitle, concerning the adulteration or misbranding of any article;
§ 21-256(4) of this subtitle, concerning the receipt in commerce of any adulterated or misbranded article;
§ 21-256(5) of this subtitle, concerning the delivery of any adulterated or misbranded article;
§ 21-258(b)(13) of this subtitle, concerning the failure to identify on a prescription form the name of the prescriber of a drug;
§ 21-258(b)(14) of this subtitle, concerning the dispensing of a drug on a written prescription that lacks the name of the prescriber; and
§ 21-258(b)(15) of this subtitle, concerning the provision to the Secretary of information about prescription drugs.
